102
00:19:33,454 --> 00:19:34,636
Excuse me.

103
00:19:37,091 --> 00:19:38,418
Sir!

104
00:19:57,144 --> 00:19:58,871
Sir.

105
00:20:00,515 --> 00:20:03,269
Look, I'm in a hurry.

106
00:20:11,159 --> 00:20:13,428
I'm no thief.

107
00:20:13,799 --> 00:20:15,754
My wife.

108
00:20:16,431 --> 00:20:18,292
She was taken.

109
00:20:20,969 --> 00:20:22,930
Down the south trail.

110
00:20:24,572 --> 00:20:26,633
By Mexicans.

111
00:20:32,013 --> 00:20:34,273
I need to get her back.

112
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:42,143
I see a rider. Three men, one woman.

113
00:20:42,340 --> 00:20:43,534
Ah-ah-ah!

114
00:20:46,111 --> 00:20:47,571
Money.

115
00:21:00,824 --> 00:21:02,618
Two.

116
00:21:03,678 --> 00:21:05,480
Five.

117
00:21:05,580 --> 00:21:07,590
No wife.

118
00:21:09,583 --> 00:21:11,344
What?

119
00:21:12,653 --> 00:21:16,115
No talk... no wife.

120
00:21:25,867 --> 00:21:28,604
Go now, or I shoot.

121
00:21:28,704 --> 00:21:30,196
Ah!

122
00:21:33,741 --> 00:21:34,945
(MOANING)

123
00:21:36,644 --> 00:21:40,139
Well, sometimes,
I just can't help myself.

124
00:21:42,984 --> 00:21:44,777
Huh.

125
00:22:21,788 --> 00:22:24,150
Hello, sir.

126
00:22:24,626 --> 00:22:27,453
Pleased to make your acquaintance.

127
00:22:30,864 --> 00:22:33,377
Just to keep you informed...

128
00:22:33,477 --> 00:22:36,621
this is my road, and as such,

129
00:22:36,721 --> 00:22:40,174
I collect a toll from all travelers
for safe passage.

130
00:22:40,274 --> 00:22:42,135
What kind of toll?

131
00:22:42,710 --> 00:22:45,029
Everything you got.

132
00:22:46,881 --> 00:22:49,366
Maybe even your soul.

133
00:22:53,053 --> 00:22:56,724
- Your horse looks real nice.
- The horse stays.

134
00:22:56,824 --> 00:22:59,328
Well, that is not your decision to make.

135
00:22:59,428 --> 00:23:01,996
You're on my road!

136
00:23:02,196 --> 00:23:04,966
And you will pay my price.

137
00:23:05,066 --> 00:23:09,386
And my price includes that horse.

138
00:23:14,842 --> 00:23:16,471
Are you lookin' to die?

139
00:23:20,415 --> 00:23:22,719
You look like you wanna die.

140
00:23:23,784 --> 00:23:25,887
You like killing unarmed men, don't you?

141
00:23:26,887 --> 00:23:28,656
(CHUCKLING)

142
00:23:28,756 --> 00:23:31,292
I just like killin' men.

143
00:23:31,392 --> 00:23:34,829
Especially when their conversation
bores me so.

144
00:23:40,802 --> 00:23:43,054
Do I know you?

145
00:23:47,108 --> 00:23:50,161
You look awful familiar to me.

146
00:23:59,654 --> 00:24:01,456
Yes.

147
00:24:01,956 --> 00:24:05,860
I think I do know you. Yes, I do.

148
00:24:08,195 --> 00:24:11,799
We look tough, we act tough,

149
00:24:11,899 --> 00:24:15,561
but in the end,
we're just lonely, scared men.

150
00:24:19,774 --> 00:24:23,037
Well, I know a soldier when I see one.

151
00:24:24,011 --> 00:24:27,197
You looking for a way to forget the war?

152
00:24:27,682 --> 00:24:30,651
Forget all the horrible,
horrible things you did.

153
00:24:30,751 --> 00:24:32,728
Shut up right now.

154
00:24:33,187 --> 00:24:35,472
Oh, I like that.

155
00:24:37,725 --> 00:24:40,668
You know, I'd like to know
more about you.

156
00:24:41,695 --> 00:24:44,799
How does it make you feel...

157
00:24:44,899 --> 00:24:47,251
when I do that?

158
00:24:50,505 --> 00:24:53,259
Answer me, goddammit!

159
00:24:56,544 --> 00:24:57,965
Open up.

160
00:25:01,148 --> 00:25:03,334
You scared?

161
00:25:03,718 --> 00:25:05,987
Well, don't be scared.

162
00:25:06,087 --> 00:25:09,657
Sometimes I think about
doing it two, three times a day.

163
00:25:10,257 --> 00:25:12,104
Ah! (GROANING)

164
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:20,652
That's my answer.

165
00:25:22,503 --> 00:25:24,639
I'm gonna kill you for that. Ah!

166
00:25:24,739 --> 00:25:26,041
Ah!

167
00:25:26,741 --> 00:25:28,226
(GRUNTING)

