than killing a man.

205
00:31:56,497 --> 00:32:00,116
Watching a man die all by himself.

206
00:32:02,503 --> 00:32:04,589
(JACKSON GASPING AND PANTING)

207
00:32:07,874 --> 00:32:10,694
Death might be a favor to you.

208
00:32:12,146 --> 00:32:14,198
(WHEEZING AND COUGHING)

209
00:32:27,061 --> 00:32:29,430
How you doing, friend?

210
00:32:29,530 --> 00:32:31,032
You still with us?

211
00:32:31,932 --> 00:32:33,984
(WHISPERING)

212
00:32:37,204 --> 00:32:38,973
What's that?

213
00:32:39,073 --> 00:32:41,109
- Fuck you.
- (CHUCKLING)

214
00:32:42,809 --> 00:32:45,812
Well, I don't know
if I can honor your dying wish,

215
00:32:45,912 --> 00:32:48,856
- which really is sad for me.
- (WHEEZING)

216
00:32:49,316 --> 00:32:51,609
Just... just kill me.

217
00:32:52,719 --> 00:32:56,590
No, no, no, no, not so fast.

218
00:32:56,690 --> 00:33:01,511
Why, this is the best moment.
Now, we don't want to rush this.

219
00:33:02,229 --> 00:33:04,281
(WHEEZING)

220
00:33:13,439 --> 00:33:17,258
Just leave... leave me alone.

221
00:33:31,225 --> 00:33:33,243
(GROANING AND SIGHING)

222
00:33:35,495 --> 00:33:37,547
(SIGHING)

223
00:33:42,369 --> 00:33:44,856
You know what I find most sad about you?

224
00:33:47,073 --> 00:33:50,086
You are all alone...

225
00:33:50,911 --> 00:33:54,698
in a world that don't celebrate
being alone.

226
00:34:10,464 --> 00:34:12,516
(BIRD TRILLING)

227
00:34:31,685 --> 00:34:33,737
(COUGHING)

228
00:34:36,590 --> 00:34:38,642
(WHEEZING)

229
00:34:42,396 --> 00:34:44,414
(GASPING)

230
00:34:51,238 --> 00:34:52,957
(GROANING)

231
00:34:55,042 --> 00:34:56,794
(CRYING OUT)

232
00:35:14,297 --> 00:35:21,103
Be thankful my son dragged you here
behind his horse.

233
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:29,966
There are stories of a killer
on the trail.

234
00:36:17,891 --> 00:36:19,910
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

235
00:36:35,342 --> 00:36:37,394
(NATIVE LANGUAGE)

236
00:36:43,784 --> 00:36:46,036
(GROANING)

237
00:36:47,724 --> 00:36:50,378
He awakens. Look at him.

238
00:36:51,028 --> 00:36:54,304
He awakens and does not know
where he is.

239
00:37:00,700 --> 00:37:02,919
Where are my guns?

240
00:37:20,006 --> 00:37:23,332
This one wants to steal a horse.

241
00:37:39,551 --> 00:37:44,437
You brought an evil white man
into our camp.

242
00:37:46,684 --> 00:37:51,188
This diseased filth needs to go.

243
00:37:51,388 --> 00:37:55,287
At the last village
they told a story about

244
00:37:55,387 --> 00:37:59,280
a killer out there killing men
and taking women.

245
00:37:59,380 --> 00:38:02,324
You saw him.

246
00:38:02,424 --> 00:38:04,610
He was possessed by evil spirits!

247
00:38:04,710 --> 00:38:06,970
Seven winters...

248
00:38:07,070 --> 00:38:09,590
Seven women.

249
00:38:10,290 --> 00:38:18,386
Father, it is my duty to honor
my commitment to save his life.

250
00:38:19,566 --> 00:38:21,962
Go on, son.

251
00:38:22,903 --> 00:38:27,609
I tried to force him into cold waters
with my bow.

252
00:38:28,033 --> 00:38:36,289
When his gun overcame me
he spared my life.

253
00:38:48,128 --> 00:38:55,344
Your foolishness has brought
a great burden.

254
00:38:56,186 --> 00:39:03,592
We will find out what kind of man
you have brought amongst us.

255
00:39:08,406 --> 00:39:11,727
Bring him to the sweat lodge.

256
00:39:15,756 --> 00:39:20,291
Let us see how the white man
likes our peyote.

257
00:39:20,391 --> 00:39:22,409
(LAUGHTER)

258
00:39:27,814 --> 00:39:29,857
(SHOUTING IN NATIVE LANGUAGE)

259
00:39:39,159 --> 00:39:42,104
What'd you... what'd you do?

260
00:39:45,499 --> 00:39:47,568
(MEN SHOUTING)

261
00:39:47,668 --> 00:39:49,703
- (PANTING)
- (GUNSHOT)

262
00:39:50,203 --> 00:39:52,255
(MEN SHOUTING)

263
00:39:57,844 --> 00:39:59,930
- (GUNSHOT)
- (MEN SCREAMING)

264
00:40:06,737 --> 00:40:08,572
