267
00:40:25,939 --> 00:40:29,196
You've got to kill yourself
to end this, Jackson.

268
00:40:29,710 --> 00:40:32,579
You need to end your own life, Jackson.

269
00:40:33,530 --> 00:40:37,117
- No.
- You were supposed to look out for me.

270
00:40:37,217 --> 00:40:39,953
You know, that's what older brothers do.

271
00:40:40,257 --> 00:40:41,921
No.

272
00:40:42,021 --> 00:40:44,207
It's time to die.

273
00:40:48,528 --> 00:40:49,586
No.

274
00:40:51,531 --> 00:40:54,263
Why'd you shoot me, Jackson?

275
00:40:55,535 --> 00:40:58,442
Your own brother, Jackson.

276
00:41:05,228 --> 00:41:07,183
No! (GRUNTING)

277
00:41:07,547 --> 00:41:11,307
I didn't mean... I didn't mean
to kill... I didn't mean to...

278
00:41:11,407 --> 00:41:13,136
No!

279
00:41:22,457 --> 00:41:27,043
This one must go now.

280
00:41:31,775 --> 00:41:35,220
This man is your responsibility.

281
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:38,146
You have honored your debt to him.

282
00:41:42,345 --> 00:41:51,270
Give him your horse so he leaves
and never comes back.

283
00:42:47,146 --> 00:42:48,531
Thank you.

284
00:43:24,479 --> 00:43:27,813
May you find your way.

285
00:43:38,514 --> 00:43:39,967
Wait.

286
00:43:59,419 --> 00:44:02,438
No. For... for you.

287
00:44:05,158 --> 00:44:07,445
Hey! Hey! Ah!

288
00:44:07,811 --> 00:44:09,978
Crazy man!

289
00:44:11,643 --> 00:44:13,929
Go now!

290
00:44:17,307 --> 00:44:21,228
Crazy man. Go. Go now!

291
00:44:22,454 --> 00:44:26,635
Crazy man! Go now!

292
00:45:27,373 --> 00:45:29,392
(WHISTLING)

293
00:45:33,513 --> 00:45:35,698
(YELLING)

294
00:45:36,349 --> 00:45:37,651
Ah!

295
00:45:38,251 --> 00:45:39,536
Ah!

296
00:47:57,523 --> 00:47:59,608
Mr. Carver?

297
00:48:02,261 --> 00:48:04,180
It's Jackson.

298
00:48:07,833 --> 00:48:10,303
You remember me?

299
00:48:10,403 --> 00:48:14,107
Yes, sir... I know who you are.

300
00:48:14,207 --> 00:48:16,459
Who could forget?

301
00:48:19,079 --> 00:48:21,982
Ah, this is my granddaughter.

302
00:48:22,482 --> 00:48:25,868
This is my acquaintance, Jackson.

303
00:48:27,186 --> 00:48:30,994
- Hello.
- Pleased to meet you.

304
00:48:31,257 --> 00:48:35,762
We served in the war together.
Rebecca lives with me now.

305
00:48:36,062 --> 00:48:37,864
How long's it been, huh?

306
00:48:37,964 --> 00:48:40,649
Hmm. Seven years in May.

307
00:48:43,169 --> 00:48:46,422
Yeah. Yeah, that's about right.

308
00:48:48,407 --> 00:48:50,410
I didn't know you had a family.

309
00:48:52,545 --> 00:48:55,815
You look like you had
a really rough journey.

310
00:48:55,915 --> 00:48:58,300
What brings you to my door?

311
00:48:58,785 --> 00:49:02,020
My wife. She's...

312
00:49:03,089 --> 00:49:05,481
She's been kidnapped.

313
00:49:06,092 --> 00:49:07,994
She's taken.

314
00:49:09,294 --> 00:49:11,147
Taken from me.

315
00:49:11,897 --> 00:49:15,951
Wife? I'm so sorry to hear that.

316
00:49:17,904 --> 00:49:21,607
Anything I can do
to get you back on the trail?

317
00:49:21,707 --> 00:49:24,394
I could use a proper saddle.

318
00:49:24,494 --> 00:49:25,729
My horse.

319
00:49:25,829 --> 00:49:29,583
Certainly. I have a small shed.
It's yours.

320
00:49:30,083 --> 00:49:34,253
Now, whatever you need. Keep the saddle.

321
00:49:34,372 --> 00:49:35,688
Thank you.

322
00:49:35,788 --> 00:49:38,173
I'll meet you over there.

323
00:50:34,580 --> 00:50:36,049
Grandfather, what's wrong?

324
00:50:36,149 --> 00:50:39,352
He's killed more men
than you met in your lifetime.

325
00:50:39,452 --> 00:50:43,557
You load your gun like I showed you,
and if anything happens to me, Rebecca,

326
00:50:43,657 --> 00:50:45,750
you will run from here.

327
00:50:45,850 --> 00:50:48,227
Do you hear me? Do as I tell you.

328
00:50:48,327 --> 00:50:52,214
You will run from this man
and you do not look back.

329
00:50:52,598 --> 00:50:54,404
Run for your life.

330
00:50:55,268 --> 00:50:57,353
Grandpa!

331
00:51:00,673 --> 00:51:04,661
You run... if anything happens to me.

332
00:51:28,034 --> 00:51:30,536
Uh, you have any...

333
00:51:30,636 --> 00:51:32,671
water for my horse?

334
00:51:33,386 --> 00:51:36,158
Pond water's not the best water.

335
00:51:36,742 --> 00:51:39,877
Follow me, son.
Let's walk down to the creek.

336
00:51:40,913 --> 00:51:43,149
So you're headed south, huh?

337
00:51:43,249 --> 00:51:45,968
- Yeah, that's right.
- Hmm.

338
00:51:46,552 --> 00:51:49,221
Saw a group of riders, uh...

339
00:51:49,321 --> 00:51:52,508
passing the big trail yesterday.

340
00:51:53,659 --> 00:51:57,213
You know, three riders
and one woman. Mexican.

341
00:51:59,098 --> 00:52:01,122
What time of day yesterday?

342
00:52:01,401 --> 00:52:03,166
Late.

343
00:52:03,266 --> 00:52:05,917
But the sun was still not down.

344
00:52:07,673 --> 00:52:09,392
Huh.

345
00:52:10,409 --> 00:52:13,512
Those Mexicans you... you saw, they...

346
00:52:13,612 --> 00:52:15,830
they took my wife.

347
00:52:16,482 --> 00:52:18,751
They came in the night
and they took her.

348
00:52:18,851 --> 00:52:22,422
Those are awful things
for any man to have to say.

349
00:52:22,522 --> 00:52:25,124
My concern is that those riders

350
00:52:25,224 --> 00:52:27,655
seemed peaceful enough.

351
00:52:28,494 --> 00:52:32,012
But they had the fear of God
in their... eyes.

352
00:52:32,112 --> 00:52:37,956
Look, I'm... I'm sorry to bring stories
of bloodshed and kidnapping to your door.

353
00:52:38,204 --> 00:52:40,873
Those things had to be said.

354
00:52:40,973 --> 00:52:43,025
Those men...

355
00:52:43,776 --> 00:52:46,858
Those men are the worst of their kind.

356
00:52:47,246 --> 00:52:51,017
Why does it strike me
that the last time I saw you...

357
00:52:51,417 --> 00:52:54,220
after some of the things you did
for General Sherman,

358
00:52:54,320 --> 00:52:56,275
the men...

359
00:52:56,375 --> 00:52:59,006
they called you Diablo?

360
00:53:00,359 --> 00:53:02,939
I asked the men what it meant.

361
00:53:03,629 --> 00:53:07,742
And when they told me...
I learned something about you.

362
00:53:08,334 --> 00:53:12,321
No. No, I was just following orders.

363
00:53:13,005 --> 00:53:16,610
I'm a married man
intent on landing my family.

364
00:53:17,610 --> 00:53:20,980
You were eventually...
Sherman's best killer,

365
00:53:21,080 --> 00:53:25,762
and as I recall, you came
to enjoy life on his trail.

366
00:53:26,652 --> 00:53:28,887
Jackson...

367
00:53:28,987 --> 00:53:32,141
I have a granddaughter in my life here.

368
00:53:33,659 --> 00:53:36,562
I was always kind to you, wasn't I?

369
00:53:36,662 --> 00:53:38,398
Yes.

370
00:53:38,898 --> 00:53:41,550
I don't mince my words.

371
00:53:42,501 --> 00:53:45,004
Why did you come here?

372
00:53:45,104 --> 00:53:47,190
I came to ask for your help.

373
00:53:48,641 --> 00:53:51,930
After all these years,
you're still torturing yourself over...

374
00:53:52,030 --> 00:53:54,047
accidentally shooting your brother?

375
00:53:56,849 --> 00:53:59,201
Go home, son.

376
00:53:59,585 --> 00:54:01,837
Leave those people alone.

377
00:54:05,024 --> 00:54:07,476
Oh, I understand.

378
00:54:07,960 --> 00:54:11,881
I fear you haven't been well
since last I seen you.

379
00:54:14,167 --> 00:54:16,927
Once you fetch the water
from that stream,

380
00:54:17,027 --> 00:54:19,521
we'll get you a proper meal.

381
00:54:20,840 --> 00:54:23,142
Then you have to go.

382
00:54:23,242 --> 00:54:25,127
Alright?

383
00:55:02,548 --> 00:55:06,847
Please! You can have anything you want,
but please don't hurt us.

384
00:55:07,620 --> 00:55:10,022
You gonna look at me like that?

385
00:55:10,122 --> 00:55:13,159
All I needed was a little bit
of fucking help from you.

386
00:55:15,094 --> 00:55:17,346
That's all I needed.

387
00:55:21,801 --> 00:55:24,304
Ah, there he is!

388
00:55:24,404 --> 00:55:26,640
Our intrepid trail traveler.

389
00:55:27,840 --> 00:55:30,526
I just can't seem to lose you.

390
00:55:31,977 --> 00:55:34,446
Well, what can I say?

391
00:55:34,546 --> 00:55:37,717
- I've become attached.
- Jackson...

392
00:55:37,817 --> 00:55:41,504
stop this insanity right now.

393
00:55:41,604 --> 00:55:44,240
Yeah, your fight's with me.

394
00:55:44,590 --> 00:55:47,155
My fight is with everybody.

395
00:55:47,493 --> 00:55:49,863
Lovely granddaughter he has in there.

396
00:55:51,063 --> 00:55:53,366
- No.
- Benjamin, how old is she?

397
00:55:53,766 --> 00:55:56,002
Please, just leave my granddaughter
alone. Please.

398
00:55:56,102 --> 00:55:57,904
Shhh. Shhh-shhh.

399
00:55:58,004 --> 00:56:02,107
Please, Jackson. I mean you no harm.

400
00:56:02,207 --> 00:56:04,176
I can help you.

401
00:56:04,276 --> 00:56:07,447
Yeah, I... I will go with you...

402
00:56:07,547 --> 00:56:10,015
and bring your wife back.

403
00:56:10,365 --> 00:56:12,851
You had your chance.

404
00:56:15,637 --> 00:56:18,190
Now say your prayers.

405
00:56:23,913 --> 00:56:25,190
Say 'em!

406
00:56:32,588 --> 00:56:35,123
For if we live...

407
00:56:35,223 --> 00:56:37,326
we live to the Lord.

408
00:56:37,426 --> 00:56:39,178
Louder.

409
00:56:39,762 --> 00:56:41,997
If we die...

410
00:56:42,097 --> 00:56:43,321
we die to the Lord.

411
00:56:43,421 --> 00:56:47,319
- Louder, goddammit! I want to hear it!
- Whether we live or we die...

412
00:56:47,419 --> 00:56:51,065
we are to the Lord!

413
00:56:51,165 --> 00:56:54,276
Our Father, who art in Heaven...

414
00:56:54,376 --> 00:56:57,610
- Louder!
- Hallowed be thy name!...

415
00:56:57,710 --> 00:57:00,754
- Louder!
- Thy Kingdom come, thy...

416
00:57:00,854 --> 00:57:04,420
- Louder, goddammit!
- Give us this day our daily bread...

417
00:57:04,520 --> 00:57:06,622
You should've never questioned me.

418
00:57:06,722 --> 00:57:11,144
- And forgive us our trespasses as...
- You better hope he's listening.

419
00:57:13,062 --> 00:57:14,847
(SCREAMING)

420
00:57:20,870 --> 00:57:22,888
(SOBBING)

421
00:57:49,065 --> 00:57:51,117
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

422
00:58:08,167 --> 00:58:09,559
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

423
00:58:35,878 --> 00:58:37,963
(WHINNYING)

424
01:00:43,877 --> 01:00:47,356
- Where is César?
- I want to leave.

425
01:00:47,764 --> 01:00:49,441
Over there.

426
01:00:53,762 --> 01:00:56,096
Let's go, César!

427
01:00:56,496 --> 01:01:00,742
Relax, Guillermo,
we are almost to the house!

428
01:01:01,557 --> 01:01:02,575
(SIGHING)

429
01:01:56,478 --> 01:01:58,525
(PANTING)

430
01:01:59,785 --> 01:02:01,527
No!

431
01:02:01,627 --> 01:02:03,301
(SCREAMING)

432
01:02:06,621 --> 01:02:08,440
No.

433
01:02:08,657 --> 01:02:11,064
- Guillermo!
- Stay!

434
01:02:11,164 --> 01:02:13,596
- Guillermo!
- Alexsandra!

435
01:02:13,696 --> 01:02:16,784
- Ah!
- Don't be afraid! Let's go!

436
01:02:17,867 --> 01:02:19,785
Guillermo!

437
01:02:44,526 --> 01:02:46,245
César! No!

438
01:02:49,797 --> 01:02:53,390
No! No! He will kill us all.

439
01:03:00,388 --> 01:03:01,919
Let's go!

440
01:03:02,019 --> 01:03:04,168
We have to get her to safety!

441
01:03:23,966 --> 01:03:27,073
- (LAUGHTER)
- (EXCITED CHATTER)

442
01:03:50,092 --> 01:03:51,544
(LAUGHTER)

443
01:04:03,393 --> 01:04:05,909
Listen! Listen!

444
01:04:06,009 --> 01:04:08,302
Get the children!

445
01:04:09,174 --> 01:04:11,530
Get into the house!

446
01:04:11,630 --> 01:04:13,338
- Fast! Fast! Fast!
- (SCREAMING)

447
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:20,318
(SCREAMING AND SHOUTING)

448
01:05:23,652 --> 01:05:25,704
(CLOCK TICKING)

449
01:06:15,504 --> 01:06:17,556
(WHISTLING)

450
01:06:21,343 --> 01:06:23,078
(WHISTLING)

451
01:06:38,193 --> 01:06:40,979
Alexsandra!

452
01:06:44,432 --> 01:06:46,518
(WHISTLING)

453
01:06:52,507 --> 01:06:54,606
(WHISTLING)

454
01:07:01,750 --> 01:07:03,835
Where is she?

455
01:07:10,592 --> 01:07:13,044
Bring her to me!

456
01:07:14,696 --> 01:07:17,715
Or I'll kill every last one of you.

457
01:07:24,139 --> 01:07:25,934
- Ah!
- (GUNFIRE)

458
01:07:27,609 --> 01:07:29,120
Ah!

459
01:07:53,615 --> 01:07:55,687
- Mama!
- (PANTING)

460
01:08:00,107 --> 01:08:02,185
- (GUNSHOT)
- (SCREAMS)

461
01:08:03,912 --> 01:08:05,481
(GROANING)

462
01:08:05,781 --> 01:08:07,458
Ah!

463
01:08:07,883 --> 01:08:10,068
(GROANING)

464
01:08:21,196 --> 01:08:23,248
(GROANING)

465
01:08:25,734 --> 01:08:27,436
(GROANING)

466
01:08:28,136 --> 01:08:30,198
- (CLICKING)
- (MAN PANTING)

467
01:08:39,269 --> 01:08:42,395
My sister will never be with you.

468
01:08:54,896 --> 01:08:57,978
That might just be a favor to you.

469
01:09:03,071 --> 01:09:04,372
(GASPING)

470
01:09:04,472 --> 01:09:05,891
Take it.

471
01:09:17,953 --> 01:09:20,435
Hmm. Yes, sir.

472
01:09:27,228 --> 01:09:30,749
We don't wanna rush this... do we?

473
01:09:33,401 --> 01:09:34,920
(SHUSHING)

474
01:09:42,010 --> 01:09:43,995
(GURGLING)

475
01:09:58,026 --> 01:10:00,045
(WHISTLING)

476
01:10:06,568 --> 01:10:08,620
(WHISTLING)

477
01:10:10,572 --> 01:10:12,624
(WHISTLING)

478
01:10:58,753 --> 01:11:00,805
(TAPPING)

479
01:11:06,161 --> 01:11:08,587
Here he comes! Here he comes! (SHUSHING)

480
01:11:12,534 --> 01:11:14,519
You go that way.

481
01:11:16,638 --> 01:11:18,890
(SCRAPING AND WHISPERING)

482
01:11:27,015 --> 01:11:28,653
(BULLETS CLATTERING)

483
01:11:50,704 --> 01:11:52,790
(CREAKING)

484
01:11:53,708 --> 01:11:55,727
(WHISTLING)

485
01:11:59,214 --> 01:12:01,299
(WHISTLING)

486
01:12:08,123 --> 01:12:10,155
(WHISTLING)

487
01:12:24,360 --> 01:12:25,638
There he is.

488
01:12:25,738 --> 01:12:27,424
Ah!

489
01:12:28,576 --> 01:12:30,395
(GROANING)

490
01:12:32,447 --> 01:12:34,332
(CRYING OUT)

491
01:12:39,087 --> 01:12:41,172
(CREAKING)

492
01:13:03,977 --> 01:13:05,386
(RATTLING)

493
01:13:09,951 --> 01:13:12,070
(SCREAMING)

494
01:13:25,633 --> 01:13:27,552
(CRACKLING)

495
01:13:28,303 --> 01:13:30,332
(DISTANT CROWING)

496
01:13:46,154 --> 01:13:47,889
(FLY BUZZING)

497
01:13:47,989 --> 01:13:49,274
(CLICKING)

498
01:13:56,230 --> 01:13:58,082
Alexsandra.

499
01:14:00,402 --> 01:14:02,287
Alexsandra!

500
01:14:03,171 --> 01:14:05,090
Alexsandra!

501
01:14:05,707 --> 01:14:06,675
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

502
01:14:06,799 --> 01:14:09,650
Why have you done this?
Guillermo's my husband.

503
01:14:10,250 --> 01:14:12,766
Come out and face me! Come out now!

504
01:14:13,481 --> 01:14:15,750
What you wanted was a fantasy.

505
01:14:15,850 --> 01:14:18,937
How many other women
have you done this to?

506
01:14:21,156 --> 01:14:23,274
Alexsandra!

507
01:14:23,858 --> 01:14:25,910
(POUNDING)

508
01:14:28,029 --> 01:14:30,882
You left me no choice.

509
01:14:32,900 --> 01:14:36,750
I... I had to have you.

510
01:14:38,706 --> 01:14:40,625
(POUNDING)

511
01:15:03,253 --> 01:15:06,183
If you touch her I will kill you!

512
01:15:09,637 --> 01:15:11,323
You poor man.

513
01:15:41,602 --> 01:15:43,658
(GUNSHOT)

514
01:15:44,106 --> 01:15:46,657
No! No! Alexsandra!

515
01:15:50,835 --> 01:15:53,911
I am going to kill you!
I am going to kill you!

516
01:15:55,416 --> 01:15:57,868
Get out of my house.

517
01:15:58,953 --> 01:16:01,443
- Go! Go!
- (CLICKING)

518
01:16:20,208 --> 01:16:23,245
No! No! No, please!

519
01:16:23,345 --> 01:16:26,432
No, don't! No!

520
01:16:26,815 --> 01:16:30,547
Stop! Stop it! No!

521
01:16:33,687 --> 01:16:36,457
Please, he's the father of my children!

522
01:16:36,557 --> 01:16:40,205
- Please don't! Guillermo!
- Alexsandra.

523
01:16:54,147 --> 01:16:57,983
I am not afraid. I am not afraid.

524
01:17:01,922 --> 01:17:03,978
Don't do it.

525
01:17:07,711 --> 01:17:09,944
We can stop.

526
01:17:11,089 --> 01:17:13,937
There does not need
to be any more death.

527
01:17:19,033 --> 01:17:21,697
ALEXSANDRA: No! No! (SCREAMING)

528
01:17:21,797 --> 01:17:24,617
- (GUNSHOT)
- (MUSIC)

529
01:21:11,098 --> 01:21:13,118
(SOFT SONG)

